  "prompt": "My son keeps getting into fights at school and bosses his siblings around whenever he's at home. How do I make him stop?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to address aggressive behavior:\n\n1. Talk to him calmly\n- Ask why he feels angry or needs to fight\n- Listen without judging\n- Help him identify and manage emotions\n\n2. Teach conflict resolution skills\n- Show him how to communicate without aggression\n- Practice problem-solving techniques\n- Encourage using words instead of physical actions\n\n3. Set clear boundaries and consequences\n- Establish rules about physical violence\n- Consistently enforce consequences for aggressive behavior\n- Praise positive interactions\n\n4. Consider professional help\n- School counselor can provide guidance\n- Child psychologist might help identify underlying issues\n- Family therapy could improve communication\n\n5. Address sibling dynamics\n- Teach respect and sharing\n- Spend one-on-one time with each child\n- Help older siblings understand leadership vs. bullying\n\n6. Check for potential triggers\n- Bullying at school\n- Stress or emotional challenges\n- Changes in family dynamics\n\n7. Model good behavior\n- Demonstrate calm conflict resolution\n- Show empathy and emotional control\n- Avoid using physical punishment\n\nWould you like to discuss these strategies in more detail?",
